description:
“Rise of the Third Army” continues!

What do you have to do to get the greedy Orange Lantern Larfleeze to share his power?

When the Third Army attacks, Larfleeze does the unthinkable and helps Kyle Rayner attempt to wield the orange power of avarice!

How can Kyle hold up his end of the bargain he struck with Larfleeze?
name: The Need for Greed

description: Following the Third World War, humankind left the toxic surface of the Earth and built an underground city to survive. A serious social problem emerged in this new society: hyperorexia, or severe overeating, a side effect of the Pure Trance life-sustaining pill. This dreamy science fiction fantasy — a sexy story of catfights, alien safari adventures, evil experimentation, and a girl who dreams of becoming a pop idol singer—is the long-awaited debut graphic novel of famous Japanese manga artist Junko Mizuno. Pure Trance breaks every stereotype of shojo manga (girls' comics).

person_credits.name: Junko Mizuno

description: Eisner Award winner SCOTT SNYDER (Batman, Swamp Thing, American Vampire), Scott Tuft & NYT Best-Selling-Artist Attila Futaki (The Lightning Thief) bring you the complete collected hardcover of the scariest horror comic of the year, SEVERED. 1916. A man haunts the roads; a man with sharp teeth and a hunger for flesh. When 12 year-old Jack Garron runs away from home, he'll see how quickly the American Dream becomes a nightmare. Collecting all 7 issues of the critically acclaimed series, and featuring never-before-seen bonus material, this hardcover deluxe version is sure to be a classic.
name: HC

description: "Space Doubles," the series Ain't it Cool News called, "a treat to read and a must-see for sci fi/horror fans" is a retro-double feature showcasing some of the hottest upcoming and established talent in comics. It is presented in flip-format with each half of the book telling an original sci-fi tale ranging from alien invasions to space flight to just about everything in between. Issue three features "Escape Pod" by Mark Andrew Smith ("Amazing Joy Buzzards") and "Everywhere I look… Bugs!" by series creator Scott Closter. In Smith's tale a young man's amnesia leads to a shocking realization, while in Closter's story, an astronaut's mind comes unraveled as everywhere he looks... BUGS!!!. Every issue also features a one page story by Brian Smith called "Pickles from Pluto."
name: Everywhere I Look... BUGS!; Escape Pod

description: The effects of McCabre’s evil plans are felt as worlds slide ever closer to the brink of destruction. Despite the best efforts of Beck and Caul, he continues to fulfill his dark pact with an evil before time. All seems lost when McCabre enthralls Caul as Beck battles his deadly hordes of monsters alone. The clock ticks ever closer to the end of creation in “The Uncreation Covenant, Part Two: What Lurks Beyond”.
name: The Uncreation Covenant, Part 2: What Lurks Beyond

description: In the fourth issue of Larry Hama's original series, The Omega Team chases Lilith to Paris, where things get deadly. When they arrive, they are faced with a deadly Golem that threatens to destroy the team and their chances of bringing the evil witch's nefarious plan to a halt.

description: After evening the score with those who betrayed him, and recovering the money he was cheated out of from the syndicate, Parker is riding high, living in swank hotels and enjoying the finer things in life again. Until, that is, he’s fingered by a squealer who rats him out to the Outfit for the price they put on his head… and they find out too late that if you push Parker, it better be all the way into the grave!
name: GN

description: His powers lost, an enemy offers to restore them, but only succeeds in driving Supreme mad. He goes on a rampage across the Image universe, battling Union, telling Spawn his story, attacking Stormwatch, and fighting Pitt.
